cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it deals with deep neural networks and their architecture search for achieving good speed and accuracy trade-off. It also involves the use of profile information for inference speed on the target platform, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper's focus on pruning and optimization techniques for neural networks makes it relevant to the neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper's application of the proposed algorithm to real-time segmentation networks suggests that it may also belong to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
